Juventus have started talks with former Tottenham Hotspur coach, Mauricio Pochettinoâ€™s representatives. According to La Stampa, Juventus board are considering appointing Pochettino to take over from current manager, Maurizio Sarri. This is coming after Monaco failed with a bid to appoint Pochettino, as their new manager. DAILY POST had reported that Monaco sacked their coach, Robert Moreno last weekend. Monaco newly-appointed sporting director, Paul Mitchell reportedly approached Pochettino about the vacant managerial role after the sacking of Moreno but the former Southampton coach rejected. Pochettino remains desperate to secure an imminent return to the English Premier League. He is waiting for the right opportunity to return to club management, after he was sacked by Spurs last November.